The subject gives basic knowledge of the malignant tumours in the maxillo-facial region. The specific characteristics and treatment modalities of these tumours are discussed. Attention is paid on the diagnosis and treatment of trigeminal and facial nerve diseases. An overview of reconstructive surgery of congenital and acquiered defects in maxillo-facial region is discussed. The course consists of the academic lectures and practical training in out- and inpatient clinic. The student has to present an academic patient case history. The clinical work performed by the student has been analyzed with the tutor, the student has received feedback and the work has been included in the student's e-portfolio.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to give basic knowledge of the malignant tumours in the maxillo-facial region, its treatment modalities and stomatological nerve diseases. To give an overview of reconstructive surgery in maxillo-facial region in case of congenital and acquiered defects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows medical deonthology 2) knows benign and malignant tumours,tumour-like lesions, precancerous lesions and stomatological nerve diseases in the maxillofacial region, knows diagnostics, clinical feature and principles of treatment of these diseases 3) is able to examine the patient, to compose the treatment plan and knows differential diagnostics of these diseases 4) knows technique of extracion in lower and and upper jaw 5) is able to perform atypical tooth, knows indications and general principles of atypical extractions and incisions on the oral mucosa 6) knows first aid and treatment of the complicated dentition of the wisdom-tooth 7) knows treatment of the operated patients, is able to give advise to the patient about treatment possibilities after procedure in maxillo-facial region 8) has to present an academic patient case history, report or scientific work
